OL,3,CMum left skipping meals as she
OL,4,Cstruggles to clothe toddler this winter
OL,6,FA mother who is studying with the
OL,7,Fhopes of becoming a midwife says she
OL,8,Fcan not afford to eat breakfast or
OL,9,Flunch as she tries to survive on just
OL,10,F#5 a week.
OL,12,FSaskia says she constantly skips meals
OL,13,Fto ensure her two-year-old daughter
OL,14,FEdie gets to eat.
OL,16,FThe 20-year-old is a single mother
OL,17,Fliving in Bristol with no family
OL,18,Fsupport. She says high nursery fees
OL,19,Fmean she is unable to work, as her
OL,20,Fchildcare bill would cost more than
OL,21,Fshe can earn.
