OL,3,CMum left skipping meals as she
OL,4,Cstruggles to clothe toddler this winter
OL,6,F"After I've paid my main bills I'm
OL,7,Fleft with about #20 a month to spend
OL,8,Fon Edie for things she needs like
OL,9,Fclothes," Saskia said. "After that, I
OL,10,Fhave no money to spend on myself. I
OL,11,Feat dinner. I don't eat breakfast and
OL,12,Flunch because it's too expensive."
OL,14,FLike every parent, Saskia said she'd
OL,15,Flove to treat her little girl.
OL,17,F"It's really difficult knowing that I
OL,18,Fdon't have all the money in the world
OL,19,Fto spoil her," she said.
OL,21,F"Especially at Christmas and birthdays.
